{{Quote|There are many factions within the Sith, each attempting to take what little remains from the Jedi Civil War.|[[Visas Marr]]|<ref name="TSL">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords]]''</ref>}}
The [[Standard year/Legends|year]] '''3955 before the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]] (BBY)''', also known as '''302 before the [[Treaty of Coruscant]] (BTC)''', was a span of time that marked the beginning of the [[Dark Wars]], following the conclusion of the [[Jedi Civil War]]. After [[Revan/Legends|Revan]] led the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] and [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] in victory over [[Darth Malak]] and the [[Darth Revan's Sith Empire|Sith Empire]], the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] remnants fractured and began to war amongst themselves. Amidst the power vacuum, Sith members became warlords, claiming small territories on the fringes of the Republic and fought for supremacy against each other in an opportunistic attempt at reviving the former glory of the Empire. At the same time, the Republic began to recover from the Jedi Civil War. In response to the [[Bombing of Telos IV|destruction]] of [[Telos IV]], [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] [[Tol Cressa|Cressa]] commenced the [[Planet/Legends|planet]]-wide [[Telosian Restoration Project]], a terraforming project aimed at making the planet habitable once again. To assist in this effort and other redevelopment projects, [[Aratech Repulsor Company/Legends|Aratech]] launched the [[G0-T0 infrastructure planning system|G0-T0 droid series]]. At the same time, the [[Kanz Disorders/Legends|Kanz Disorders]], a secessionist movement in the [[Kanz sector/Legends|Kanz sector]], was still ongoing. Consumed by the recent wars and recovery, the Republic had not intervened in the conflict.

==Proem==
{{Quote|The Jedi Civil War brought much suffering to the galaxy, and the forces that Malak and Revan amassed against us seemed limitless. Many worlds were destroyed, trade routes disrupted, and the Republic fleet was almost decimated. While it is said that Revan and several Republic heroes and Jedi defeated Malak, in many ways Malak had already won.|Mical|<ref name="TSL" />}}
{{SeeAlso|Jedi Civil War|3956 BBY}}
The [[Jedi Civil War]] was a [[The galaxy/Legends|galaxy]]-wide conflict that followed in the wake of the also devastating [[Mandalorian Wars]]. The combination of two wars left the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] reeling in commercially, politically, and militarily.<ref name="TSL" /> Even though the Republic had defeated [[Darth Malak]]'s [[Darth Revan's Sith Empire|Sith Empire]] at the [[Battle of Rakata Prime]] in [[3956 BBY]], the effects were far-flung.<ref name="KotORCG" /> Worlds, such as [[Telos IV|Telos]] and [[Taris/Legends|Taris]], had been destroyed through [[Orbital bombardment/Legends|orbital bombardment]]; trade routes and infrastructure had been disrupted or destroyed which allowed for various [[Hutt Cartel/Legends|Hutt Cartels]] or criminal organizations such as the [[Exchange]] to manipulate markets and hoard goods; in addition, the military which defended the Republic was on the verge of collapse. Similarly, the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] was in disarray from having lost many members through defection and battle.<ref name="TSL" />

The hero of the war was [[Revan/Legends|Revan]], the former [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord]] who ruled the empire until being [[Capture of Darth Revan|captured]] in [[3957 BBY]].<ref name="KotORCG" /> Having been redeemed, Revan successfully led the Republic to victory, creating a power vacuum in the Sith ranks.<ref name="TSL" />

==The galaxy in 3955 BBY==
===Galactic Republic===
[[File:TelosIV.png|thumb|left|175px|[[Telos IV]] during the [[Telosian Restoration Project|restoration]]]]
{{Quote|The surface of Telos was destroyed during the Jedi Civil War a few years ago. This &ndash; Citadel Station &ndash; is part of the Republic's planetary restoration initiative.|Moza|<ref name="TSL" />}}
{{SeeAlso|Telosian Restoration Project}}
Due to the devastation from the recent wars, [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] [[Tol Cressa]] began large-scale rebuilding initiatives. One such was the [[Telosian Restoration Project]],<ref name="NEGD" /> a terraforming program designed to make the [[Planet/Legends|world]] habitable following its [[Bombing of Telos IV|destruction]]<ref name="TSL" /> in [[3958 BBY]].<ref name="KotORCG" /> For the Telos venture and other reconstruction efforts, the company [[Aratech Repulsor Company/Legends|Aratech]] launched the [[G0-T0 infrastructure planning system|G0-T0 droid series]]. Round black droids, they were designed to carry out tasks of planetary administration within the confines of both Republic law and what would only benefit the project. While a [[G0-T0]] droid was used in the administration of Telos,<ref name="NEGD" /> the responsible party for the Restoration Project was the [[Ithorian/Legends|Ithorian]] [[Chodo Habat's herd|herd]] of [[Chodo Habat]]. The herd divided the planet into different [[Restoration Zone|zones]], gradually healing the planet one portion at a time. Above Telos, the large [[Citadel Station]] was constructed to house all the operations along with the necessary business needed to accommodate the large number of employees. Moreover, the project as a whole was a test pilot to see if such an undertaking was possible on other devastated worlds.<ref name="TSL" />

Around this year, a [[Gelesi's daughter|daughter]] was born to [[Gelesi]], a [[Onderon Soldier|soldier]] serving in the [[Onderon/Legends|Onderonian]] [[Onderonian military|military]].<ref name="KotORCG" /><ref name="TSL" /> In addition, the [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'lek]] [[Mission Vao]] and her [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] companion, [[Zaalbar]], established a successful shipping business.<ref name="Revan">''[[The Old Republic: Revan]]''</ref>

===Sith Empire remnant===
{{Quote|After the Jedi Civil War it took a year or two for the Republic to send a force here to deal with any Sith that may have remained. They found Korriban much as we have. Barren and lifeless. And no Sith at all.|[[Kreia]], to the [[Meetra Surik|Jedi Exile]]|<ref name="TSL" />}}
{{SeeAlso|Dark Wars}}
The year 3955 BBY marked the beginning of the [[Dark Wars]], a series of smaller conflicts and skirmishes that stemmed from the Sith defeat at [[Lehon/Legends|Rakata Prime]].<ref name="KotORCG" /> The defeat of Darth Malak had left a vacuum, and power struggles ensued resulting in the quickly escalating [[Sith Civil War]]. The Sith remnant fractured the remaining strongholds of the Sith Empire into smaller territories. Declaring themselves sovereign warlords, they began to make war on each other with the goal of gaining or retaining whatever power they had.<ref name="KotORCG" /><ref name="TSL" /> On [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]], however, the [[Skirmish on Korriban|destruction]] of the [[Sith Academy (Korriban)|Sith Academy]] resulted in an insurrection there. The warring Sith massacred each other and the planet was left barren and lifeless. About this time, an [[Expedition to Korriban|expedition]] to the planet by Republic forces to root out any remaining Sith found it void of [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] life.<ref name="TSL" />

===Kanz sector===
{{SeeAlso|Kanz Disorders/Legends}}
Along the fringes of Republic space, in the [[Kanz sector/Legends|Kanz sector]],<ref name="NEC" /> the secessionist [[Myrialites]] had created an independent government during the [[3970 BBY|height]] of the [[Mandalorian Wars]].<ref name="DSPL">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/fiction/feature20090531/index.html?page=1|text=Death in the Slave Pits of Lorrd: A Hyperspace Exclusive|int=Death in the Slave Pits of Lorrd}}</ref> The secessionist movement, called the [[Argazdan Redoubt]], continued to conquer the Kanz sector abated and subjugate the peoples of the worlds, putting many into [[Slavery/Legends|slavery]].<ref name="DSPL" /> Following the Jedi Civil War, the Republic still had not intervened in the conflict.<ref name="NEC" /> One such peoples, the [[Lorrdian/Legends|Lorrdians]], began to develop [[Kinetic communication|alternate forms]] of communication during this time in order to communicate against the will of their masters.<ref name="DSPL" />

==Impact==
[[File:TrayusCore.jpg|thumb|right|175px|The core of the [[Trayus Academy]] on [[Malachor V]]]]
{{Quote|To be united by hatred is a fragile alliance at best.|Kreia|audio=KreiaFragileAlliance.flac|<ref name="TSL" />}}
{{SeeAlso|First Jedi Purge|Sith Civil War}}
The Telosian Restoration Project was not immune to corruption or scandal. Within [[3951 BBY|four years]], [[Czerka Arms/Legends|Czerka Corporation]], a weapons manufacturer and commodities supplier, began trying to usurp control over the project from the Ithorian herd using bribery and other less-than legal means. Underworld criminal organizations, such as the Exchange, also began operations on Telos in an attempt to capitalize on the inflow of materials for the project.<ref name="TSL" /> The G0-T0 droid assigned to the project confronted a paradox in its programming. The droid calculated that it was unable to benefit the project and the Republic without breaking the law. It eventually broke through its programming, becoming fully autonomous, and began to act illegally to bring about what it calculated as the best course for the Republic's efforts.<ref name="NEGD" />

Elsewhere, the Sith continued to war against each other. [[Kreia|Darth Traya]], formerly known as Kreia, eventually began to train [[Darth Nihilus]] and [[Darth Sion]] at her [[Trayus Academy|academy]] on [[Malachor V]]. The three Sith Lords formed a frailly constructed [[Sith Triumvirate|triumvirate]] and consolidated power among the remaining factions. In [[3954 BBY]], Sion unleashed a wave of agents throughout the galaxy to begin [[First Jedi Purge|eliminating]] the remaining Jedi.<ref name="TSL" /> At the same time, the [[Kanz Disorders/Legends|Kanz Disorders]] continued unabated. The slavery and subjugation lasted nearly three hundred more years<ref name="DSPL" /> until [[3670 BBY]].<ref name="NEC" />

==Notable events==
*Supreme Chancellor Cressa starts the Telosian Restoration Project, for which Aratech launches the G0-T0 droid series.<ref name="NEGD" />
*The Dark Wars begin.<ref name="KotORCG" />

==Behind the scenes==
The events of 3955 BBY were first described in relation to the conclusion of the Jedi Civil War in the [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords]]'', although the exact date of "3955 BBY" is not provided therein.<ref name="TSL" /> ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' and [[Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force (real-life book)|''Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force'']] establish the Jedi Civil War as ending in [[3956 BBY]] and further expand on events that occurred thereafter.<ref name="NEC" /><ref name="JvS">[[Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force (real-life book)|''Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force'']]</ref> The first explicit mention of the date 3955 BBY, however, appears in ''[[The New Essential Guide to Droids]]'', which was published in June of 2006.<ref name="NEGD" /> The events depicted in ''The Sith Lords'' and the ''Essential Guides'' were largely confirmed to have taken place in 3955 BBY with the publication of the ''[[Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide]]'' by [[Wizards of the Coast]].<ref name="KotORCG" /> Most recently, the details of the Kanz Disorders are described in greater detail in the [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|''Hyperspace'']]-published short story ''[[Death in the Slave Pits of Lorrd]]''.<ref name="DSPL" /> Previously, limited information was only provided by brief mention in [[The Essential Chronology (real-world book)|''The Essential Chronology'']], although without dating the conflict, and ''The New Essential Chronology''.<ref name="NEC" /><ref name="EC">[[The Essential Chronology (real-world book)|''The Essential Chronology'']]</ref>

